240 /** Checks if the nth field in a record is a character type field which extends
241 the nth field in tuple, i.e., the field is longer or equal in length and has
242 common first characters.
243 @param[in] tuple data tuple
244 @param[in] rec record
245 @param[in] offsets array returned by rec_get_offsets()
246 @param[in] n compare nth field
247 @param[in] index index where the record resides
248 @return true if rec field extends tuple field */
249 static bool page_cur_rec_field_extends(const dtuple_t *tuple, const rec_t *rec,
250 const ulint *offsets, ulint n,
251 const dict_index_t *index) {
252 const dtype_t *type;
253 const dfield_t *dfield;
254 const byte *rec_f;
255 ulint rec_f_len;
256
257 ut_ad(rec_offs_validate(rec, NULL, offsets));
258 dfield = dtuple_get_nth_field(tuple, n);
259
260 type = dfield_get_type(dfield);
261
262 rec_f = rec_get_nth_field_instant(rec, offsets, n, index, &rec_f_len);
263
264 if (type->mtype == DATA_VARCHAR || type->mtype == DATA_CHAR ||
265 type->mtype == DATA_FIXBINARY || type->mtype == DATA_BINARY ||
266 type->mtype == DATA_BLOB || DATA_GEOMETRY_MTYPE(type->mtype) ||
267 type->mtype == DATA_VARMYSQL || type->mtype == DATA_MYSQL) {
268 if (dfield_get_len(dfield) != UNIV_SQL_NULL && rec_f_len != UNIV_SQL_NULL &&
269 rec_f_len >= dfield_get_len(dfield)
270 /* is_ascending parameter in the below call is passed as a
271 constant as we are only testing for equality and we are
272 not interested in what the nonzero return value actually
273 is. */
274 &&
275 !cmp_data_data(type->mtype, type->prtype, true, dfield_get_data(dfield),
276 dfield_get_len(dfield), rec_f, dfield_get_len(dfield))) {
277 return true;
278 }
279 }
280
281 return false;
282 }
